(324, 45, 543, 'Operating system: It\'s a system software that handles hardware, manages resources, and offers services to programs.', '2025-12-29 22:59:26'),
(325, 45, 544, 'Main functions: Includes process control, memory handling, file system, device coordination, and security.', '2025-12-29 22:59:26'),
(326, 45, 545, 'Process states: New (being created), Ready (waiting for CPU), Running (executing instructions).', '2025-12-29 22:59:26'),
(327, 45, 546, 'Multitasking vs Multithreading: Multitasking runs many programs; multithreading splits one program into threads.', '2025-12-29 22:59:26'),
(328, 45, 547, 'Deadlock: When processes wait forever for each other\'s resources. Needs: mutual exclusion, hold & wait, no preemption, circular wait.', '2025-12-29 22:59:26'),
(329, 45, 548, 'FCFS: First process in line gets CPU. Pros: simple, fair. Cons: slow for short tasks.', '2025-12-29 22:59:26'),
(330, 45, 549, 'Virtual memory: Lets big programs run by using disk space. Done via paging and segmentation.', '2025-12-29 22:59:26'),
(331, 45, 550, 'Paging: Breaks memory into pages and frames. Page table maps them.', '2025-12-29 22:59:26'),
(332, 45, 551, 'Semaphore: Tool for sync. Binary = 0/1; Counting = tracks multiple resources.', '2025-12-29 22:59:26'),
(333, 45, 552, 'Process vs Thread: Process is independent; thread shares memory inside process.', '2025-12-29 22:59:26'),
(334, 45, 553, 'Fragmentation: Wasted memory. Internal = unused inside blocks; External = scattered free space.', '2025-12-29 22:59:26'),
(335, 45, 554, 'Interrupts: Signals that pause current task to handle urgent stuff.', '2025-12-29 22:59:26'),
(336, 45, 555, 'System calls: Interface to OS. Examples: fork(), exec().', '2025-12-29 22:59:26'),
(337, 45, 556, 'Scheduling types: Preemptive = OS can interrupt; Non-preemptive = process runs till done.', '2025-12-29 22:59:26'),
(338, 45, 557, 'File allocation: Contiguous = file stored in continuous blocks. Fast but can waste space.', '2025-12-29 22:59:26'),
(339, 51, 543, 'Operating system: Software that manages hardware and gives services to apps.', '2025-12-29 23:02:36'),
(340, 51, 544, 'Functions: Process scheduling, memory control, file access, device usage, and protection.', '2025-12-29 23:02:36'),
(341, 51, 545, 'Process states: New (just created), Ready (waiting), Running (executing).', '2025-12-29 23:02:36'),
(342, 51, 546, 'Multitasking vs Multithreading: Multitasking = multiple programs; Multithreading = multiple threads in one program.', '2025-12-29 23:02:36'),
(343, 51, 547, 'Deadlock: Processes stuck waiting. Needs: mutual exclusion, hold & wait, no preemption, circular wait.', '2025-12-29 23:02:36'),
(344, 51, 548, 'FCFS: First come, first served. Good: easy. Bad: long wait for short jobs.', '2025-12-29 23:02:36'),
(345, 51, 549, 'Virtual memory: Uses disk as extra memory. Done by paging/segmentation.', '2025-12-29 23:02:36'),
(346, 51, 550, 'Paging: Splits memory into fixed pages. Page table links logical to physical.', '2025-12-29 23:02:36'),
(347, 51, 551, 'Semaphore: Sync tool. Binary = 0 or 1; Counting = tracks multiple resources.', '2025-12-29 23:02:36'),
(348, 51, 552, 'Process vs Thread: Process = full program; Thread = part of process.', '2025-12-29 23:02:36'),
(349, 51, 553, 'Fragmentation: Memory waste. Internal = inside blocks; External = scattered gaps.', '2025-12-29 23:02:36'),
(350, 51, 554, 'Interrupts: Signals to stop current task and do something urgent.', '2025-12-29 23:02:36'),
(351, 51, 555, 'System calls: Way for programs to ask OS. Examples: fork(), exec().', '2025-12-29 23:02:36'),
(352, 51, 556, 'Scheduling: Preemptive = OS interrupts; Non-preemptive = process finishes first.', '2025-12-29 23:02:36'),
(353, 51, 557, 'File allocation: Contiguous = blocks next to each other. Fast but can cause fragmentation.', '2025-12-29 23:02:36'),
